comment._content: Douglas AD-5W / EA-1E Skyraider Bu No 135977 In Light Gull Gray and insignia white with squadron code GD of Carrier Airborne Early Warning Squadron Thirty-Three (VAW-33) on tail and starboard wing plus Modex number 886 on engine cowling. The serial number is within known AD-5W production batches. The AD-5W / EA-1E was an early warning version of the AD-5 with a large AN/APS-20 search radar in a radome underneath the fuselage and seated an extra two crew members beneath a bulged aluminum rear canopy. The radome made the aircraft bulkier, less maneuverable and caused a higher stall speed than other Skyraiders. AD-5Ws were redesignated EA-1E from September 1962. EA-1E Skyraider Bu No 135977 is recorded as arriving on 4 October 1966, into desert storage at the then MASDC, Fate Unknown. Possibly broken up for salvage. Dedicated VA(AW)-33 / VAW-33 / VAQ-33 website: www.reenactor.net/vaq-33/vaq-33_history.html
